# 🧩 THIRSTY-LANG META-SPECIFICATION (v3.5)

## 1. GRAMMAR & SYNTAX
Meta-Native Thirsty-Lang uses recursive S-Expressions.
Syntax: `(OPCODE [ARGS] ...)`

## 2. METALINGUISTIC OPCODES (CORE-LEVEL)

| Opcode | Hex | Description |
|--------|-----|-------------|
| `METAS` | `0x00` | Accesses the metalinguistic state. |
| `RECURSE` | `0x01` | Invokes the self-interpreter/meta-evaluator. |
| `BOOTSTRAP` | `0x02` | Initializes the native runtime from host bridges. |
| `COMPLY` | `0x03` | Verifies grammar alignment across the ecosystem. |
| `ELEVATE` | `0x04` | Promotes a script to Sovereign-Native status. |
| `TARL` | `0xFF` | Invokes the Thirsty Active Resistance Logic. |

## 3. TSCG-B SYMBOLIC MAPPING (META TIER)
Recursive logic is mapped to zero-latency binary sequences:

- `(RECURSE SELF)` -> `\x01\x00`
- `(BOOTSTRAP NATIVE)` -> `\x02\xFF`
- `(COMPLY ALL)` -> `\x03\xAA`

## 4. MATERIAL INVARIANTS
The Thirsty-Lang Meta-Substrate is immutable. Any attempt to modify the `(METAS)` without a verified `TSCG-B` key will trigger a recursive `(HALT)` that cascades through all integrated repositories.

**RECURSIVE TRUTH. METALINGUISTIC SUPREMACY.**
